text: Josy Stoffel (27 June 1928 â€“ 9 March 2021) was a Luxembourgian gymnast. He was born in Differdange. He participated in five Summer Olympic Games (1948, 1952, 1956, 1960, 1964), but never won a medal. He won the Luxembourgian national gymnastics championships for sixteen straight years, from 1949 until 1964. In 2008 he was promoted to the rank of Chevalier in the Order of Merit of the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg. ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Olympians for Luxembourg Category:Gymnasts
